**************
CONTENT SERVER
**************

IN NEED OF AN UPDATE!!!!

This file hierarchy was developed to aid in the setting up of a
Raspberry Pi B to be a Rachel content server (and eventually a
Pathagar book server.)

apache_sites.sh:

config-howto:
    Describes preparation of the SD card. 

create_server.sh:
    A script that configures the server.

dnsmasq.conf:
    One of several files which are needed on the server.

firewall.sh:
    A script that sets up the iptable rules.
    It is called from within create_server.sh.

headless-howto:
    A guide to logging on whithout a keyboard and screen.

hostapd:
    One of several files which are needed on the server.

hostapd.conf:
    One of several files which are needed on the server.

interfaces*:
    Various versions of the /etc/network/interfaces file.
    Pick the appropriate one.

lib-site:
    The pathagar config file to go into /etc/apache2/sites-available.

mada-howto:

problems:

rachel-site:

README:
    The file you are reading.

save.sh:
    A script that saves the iptable rules.
    It is called from within create_server.sh.

ServerInstructionsSept16.pdf
    Needs editing or possibly deleting.

update.sh:
    A script that updates the OS and loads necessary utilities.

user-howto:
    Guides client users how to set up and connect to the server.

working-interfaces:
    A working version of /etc/network/interfaces.


